ies).\n[former/alt detail] Now the Institute of Living (Hartford Hospital campus)"},"INST022":{"id":"INST022","primary_name":"American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions","name":"American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions","alt_names":["ABCFM","American Board"],"type":"missionary_society","founding_year":1810,"location":{"city":"Boston","state":"Massachusetts"},"primary_persons":["X00724"],"hooker_connected_people":["X00724","X02121","X02122","T01213","H00527","I01195"],"person_ids":[],"related_institutions":[],"related_landmarks":[],"tags":["native_american_contact","missionary"],"sources":[{"short":"Wikipedia","note":"Elias Cornelius (clergyman); ABCFM"}],"notes":"First American foreign-mission organization. Tree connections: Rev. Elias Cornelius (agent 1816, secretary 1831-32); Ainsworth and Harriet Ellsworth Blunt, missionaries to the Cherokee at Brainerd, Tennessee; Eliza Talcott, missionary to Japan; Rev. William Banfield Capron, Madura mission; Judge John Hooker, member."},"INST122":{"id":"INST122","primary_name":"Yale School of Medicine (Medical Institution of Yale College)","name":"Yale School of Medicine (Medical Institution of Yale College)","alt_names":[],"type":"university","founding_year":1810,"location":{"city":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yale_School_of_Medicine","primary_persons":[],"hooker_connected_people":["H01407","HD0786","HD1248","HD1258","HD1530","HD1552","HD2755","H01447","HD3015","TD0066","T01047","T02264","HD3158","I00322","HD3395","HD3396","HD3397","I00334","I00357"],"person_ids":["X02790"],"related_institutions":[],"related_landmarks":[],"tags":[],"sources":[],"notes":"Founded 1810 as the Medical Institution of Yale College, the fourth oldest medical school in the United States.\n\n[Stage 6Y-211 data integrity audit: hooker_connected_people populated from systematic tree-wide search of education/career/research_notes fields. 20 documented tree